‪Nigeria recorded few new cases of Coronavirus on Friday, bringing the total number of COVID-19 cases in the country to 70.‬ ‪Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), made this known via its twitter handle on Friday. ‬ ‪Three out of the new case were recorded in Abuja, while the other two were recorded in Oyo state, according to the NCDC. ‬ ‪The tweet read, “Five new cases of #COVID19 have been reported in Nigeria: 3 in FCT & 2 in Oyo State”‬ “As at 08:00 pm 27th March there are 70  cases of  confirmed #COVID19 reported Nigeria. 3 have been discharged with 1 death.”